The paper deals with link adaptation in wireless communication, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed algorithm also involves computing outage probability and expected throughput, which are concepts related to system engineering (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the algorithm in a specific channel model, which falls under the category of computer engineering (cs.CE).
